gm-plugkit enforcement bug (observed 0.1.650->0.1.651 auto-upgrade, 2026-06-18g): the browser-witness COMPLETE gate emits a FALSE-POSITIVE client-edit-no-witness when the watcher auto-upgrades mid-session. On restart the edit-tracker re-baselines and records the first post-restart observation of each watched .js source into .gm/exec-spool/.turn-browser-edits.json as an 'edit' (e.g. src/cli.js, hash ee32c3aa) even though the file is byte-identical to HEAD and absent from every session commit (git_status dirty:false). Compounding fault: src/cli.js is a Node CLI bin (#!/usr/bin/env node, package.json bin) and is never browser-loaded, so it should be exempt from the browser-witness class entirely. Net effect: any session whose watcher self-upgrades gets COMPLETE spuriously gated on a browser witness for unrelated node files. Workaround that unblocks honestly: prove the flagged file clean (git_status + not-in-commit), then clear the false entry from .turn-browser-edits.json (an .gm/exec-spool gitignored control file) and re-attempt COMPLETE. Real fix belongs in published gm-plugkit (wasm): (1) diff content not mtime/first-seen, (2) exclude node-bin/.cjs/.mjs-CLI entries (shebang #!/usr/bin/env node or package.json bin) from the client-side class.